					<head>Pentateuch scroll</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420   lccn.loc.gov/sh85118979" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Pentateuch scroll. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="2v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר תורה</title>
							<note>
								<p>Breaks off with Deuteronomy 32:49. </p>
								<p>Verses 44-47 following the Song Ha᾿azinu in Deuteronomy 32 arranged in six lines. </p>
								<p>The Song of Moses, Exodus 15, and the five lines of text preceding and following it, occupy a separate column. </p>
								<p>In Leviticus 10:16 both דרש are written in the middle of the line. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 16th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>66 membranes, 234 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>468</height>
										<width>36820</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>66 membranes, with wrapper/header (706mm long). </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Old repairs. </p>
									<p>Slight mould mottling in places. </p>
									<p>A few tears. </p>
									<p>Some edge damage and dirt. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="234" ruledLines="42" writtenLines="42">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point.</p>
									<p>Visible stiching. </p>
									<p>234 columns in total, two to five columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on בדהיחק. The letter ח arched throughout. </p>
									<p>Several majuscular and minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>Special shape of the letter ו occurs in Num. 25:12, and inverted נ is placed before and after Num. 10:35-36. </p>
									<p>The &quot;puncta extraordinaria&quot; placed on the words fixed by masorah. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
